Class Dot

java.lang.Object
GameUnit
Dot
public class Dot extends GameUnit
The Dot class represents different types of dots in the game. It inherits from the GameUnit class and provides functionality for dot objects. Dots can have different types, such as normal dots, cherries, or pellets. Example Usage: Dot dot = new Dot(100, 200); dot.DrawFixUnit();
Author:
YongchunLi
